Semaphore supports the following Java versions:

<% package_versions("java").each do |version| %>
  - <%= version %>
<% end %>

Switching between Java versions is done by adding the following command to your
build commands:

`echo 1 | sudo update-alternatives --config java`

Replace the number after the echo with the desired Java version's ordinal number
from the table below. The default is `openjdk-7`.

```
There are 2 choices for the alternative java (providing /usr/bin/java).
Selection Path Priority Status
-----------------------------------------------------------
0 /usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/jre/bin/java 1072 auto mode
* 1 /usr/lib/jvm/java-7-openjdk-amd64/jre/bin/java 1071 manual mode
2 /usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/jre/bin/java 1072 manual mode
```

